Calm and Rainy.
The wind North West worked on vessel ready to go to loading
The wind West N West in forenoon W. S. W in afternoon left home at 2 oclock pm for East Sullivan to load with staves for Rockland, arrived at dark and hauled into the wharf
The wind North West commenced loading got hold full staves
The wind Westerly finished loading at 2 oclock P.M. and hauled of from wharf at 8 PM and anchored
The wind North East in morning very light came out of Sullivan in morning took the wind South West in afternoon and got home at sunset
The wind W. S. W. went gunning on rock and Ledges got 4 birds
location: Winter Harbor, Egg Rock, Winter Harbor
notes: Does not specify egg rock, but I have a feeling that there are several egg rock, there is one egg rock and ledge north of North Haven but that seems far.

journal_entry: The wind very moderate westerly foggy
The wind South West and foggy made decoys for Geo Gerrish and dug potatoes wrote letter to Thomas Bunker.

The wind Southerly and foggy bought a stick of Win Rand to make a flying jib boom in forenoon and went to work making it with J. f. Kingsley in afternoon wrote letters to Robt Miles and Nickerson and Rideout
finished flying jibboom in forenoon and carried it on board The wind out foggy
The wind S. S. East  very moderate made decoys for Geo .Gerrish
The wind Westerly made martin gill for vessel and covered Lounge for my self
The wind West South W. fitted rigging on flying jibboom and bent flying jib.
The wind North West in morning got under way in the morning for Rockland in the afternoon the wind hauled South W.  by. W. anchored in Bass Harbor at 4 p.m.
The wind from East to North moderate got under way at day light and anchored in Fox Islands at dark
The wind abt. S. W. got under way in morning for Rockland beat to the Sugar loaves blew very heavy could not get by the Fiddler and went back to Fox Island.
location: Fox Islands, Fiddler Ledge, Fox Islands

journal_entry: The wind South West got under way in the morning and went to Rockland hauled into the wharf at night and took of apart of the dockload.
The wind South West finished onloading and got freight  money
The wind South West in morning got under way for home. the wind hauled to the West squally and rainy in the afternoon the wind hauled to the North West heavy breeze got home at dark
The wind Northerly hauled into the wharf recd letter from Thomas Bunker
The wind Southerly
Very moderate all day with the wind Westerly worked on vessel wrote letter to the Hancock Co Pub Co.
The wind N West very fresh breeze hauled from wharf and worked 1/2 day on vessels wheel
The wind South West left home in the morning for Sullivan at noon took the wind N. W. got to Sullivan at 3 pm and went into the wharf
The wind North West blowed heavy began to load with staves in afternoon got half hold full
The wind North West heavy breeze finished the hold in forenoon and hauled from wharf at noon
The wind Northerly and cold loaded to the scow with wood and took her of
The wind very moderate all day and cold from the westward Ice made all day took of one scow load of wood.
The wind South West got of one scow load of wood
Calm in morning Southerly in afternoon got apart of scow load of wood and finished loading rain and blow in evening
The wind Northerly got under way in forenoon and went home
The wind W. N. W. heavy blow laid at anchor in Winter Harbor
The wind South East left home at 9 am for Rockland and anchored at Fox Island at dark raining.
The wind E. N. E. in morning snowing heavy blow. N. N. W. in afternoon laid at anchor
The wind N. N. W. got underway in the afternoon for Rockland passed Owl's head at sunset got into Rockland at 4 p.m.
The wind abt. East very heavy blow and snow storm in morning and rain at night
The wind West heavy blow hauled into David Ames wharf and sold deckload and discharged it. wrote letter home
The wind Westerly and moderate hauled into the Wilson wharf at the point Cobb Lime Co. and discharged. most of the hold full of staves recd letter from Joy and Hutchings.
Thanks Giving The wind Westerly finished onloading and took in freight for Sullivan
The wind Northerly Came out of Rockland at One A. M. very moderate wind baffling. at sunrise passed the fiddler. took the wind S. S. W. at Channel rock got home at 2 p.m.
location: Rockland, Fiddler Ledge, Channel Rock, Winter Harbor

journal_entry: The wind Southerly and warm recd letter from Peleg Tracy took freight out of the vessel
The wind South Easterly very fresh breeze and very heavy rain
The wind W. N. W. heavy blow. laid at anchor. very cold
The wind Northerly in morning got underway for East Sullivan. The wind Southerly in afternoon got to the wharf in East Sullivan at dark snow and rain in Evening.
The wind Westerly discharged freight.
The wind Westerly commenced loading took in 5 cords of wood
The wind Northerly took of 9 cords of wood in scow
The wind very moderate Northerly in morning took of one scow load of wood Southerly wind in afternoon
The wind Northerly in morning very moderate then calm in afternoon very light air to the South got underway abt. noon went into Point Harbor snowing at dark
The wind North Easterly very moderate with fine rain got under way in morning for home. drifted ashore on from Iron Bound at noon came of at 9 PM and went into Stave Island
location: Harbor Point, Iron Bound, Stave Island

journal_entry: The wind North and overcast. got under way in morning for home arrived at 9 am. got water and provision on board and got ready to go to Rockland wrote letter to Thomas Bunker
The wind Northerly in morning got underway and started for Rockland took the wind South West and went back
The wind North West got underway got under way in fore-noon and anchored in Buckle Island Harbor at 4 p.m.
The wind South Easterly got underway at day light  fresh breeze and snow sqalls clerned up at 8 am and shut down thick with snow. at 12 oclock and arrived in Rockland at 12 m.
The wind Westerly sold wood to William's and Dean Hauled into the wharf at noon and commenced to discharge in afternoon
The wind Westerly. laid along side the wharf the wind Easterly in evening with light snow
The wind North Easterly very moderate snow storm. cleared up in the afternoon the wind hauled to the North very cold finished onloading.
The wind North West very cold hauled to Birds wharf to take in corn and meal.
The wind Westerly filled hold with freight for E. Sullivan
The wind S. S. W. came out of Rockland at day light got home at dark
The wind North West cold
The wind W. N. West quite moderate took freight out of vessel in forenoon and went to East Sullivan to land freight.
Calm all day landed freight for Walter McCrate in Boat to much ice to get to the wharf.
The wind North and cold laid still
The wind Northerly and very cold in morning South West and rain at night landed freight for Geo Bunker in boat
The wind very moderate Northerly boating ashore corn and meal
Calm in morning finished boating corn and settled freight in forenoon. The wind South and rainy in afternoon got underway and beat home arrived at dark
The wind North West Christmas work in shop
Calm all day got chest out the Sea Flower getting ready to have up
Very moderate to the Westward in morning
The wind S. S. West and rainy worked in shop
The wind Westerly hauled along side of the Brig John Aviles and took over 46 bbls flour for South West Harbor.
location: Winter Harbor, Southwest Harbor, Winter Harbor

journal_entry: The wind North West heavy blow and cold worked on board vessel in forenoon. put coal fixturs in stove and commenced burning coal in afternoon.
The wind North West dreadful heavy blow and very cold staid in house and taped boots
NA
